==Organised Zombies?==
===Talking to Elias White===
* {{tcond|If the player did not speak to Elias at the [[Uzer Oasis]] prior to 21 February 2024:}}
** '''Player:''' Hello there.
** '''Elias White:''' Good day to you.
** '''Player:''' What brings you here?
** '''Elias White:''' The eternal quest for knowledge, of course! The name's Elias White. I'm something of an explorer.
** '''Player:''' Pleased to meet you. I'm [player name]. So you're searching for knowledge in an inn?
** '''Elias White:''' Not exactly. In fact, I was previously hunting down information on an ancient race deep within the desert.
** '''Elias White:''' However, I received an interesting yet concerning tip- off from a contact of mine regarding some of my research. I came here to investigate for myself.
** {{tact|continue}}
* {{tcond|If the player spoke to Elias at the Uzer Oasis before 21 February 2024:}}
** '''Elias White:''' Oh, hello there. You look familiar. Have we met before?
** '''Player:''' I think so. The name's [player name]. You're Elias, right? You had a camp out near Uzer.
** '''Elias White:''' Ah, of course. You offered to help with my work, didn't you? I'm still very keen to take you up on that offer at some point, but a more pressing matter has delayed that somewhat.
** '''Player:''' Is that what's brought you here?
** '''Elias White:''' Indeed. I recived an interesting yet concerning tip-off from a contact of mine regarding some of my research. I came here to investigate for myself.
** {{tact|continue}}
* '''Player:''' Anything I can help with?
* {{tcond|If the player does not meet the quest's requirements:}}
** '''Elias White:''' How kind of you to offer. I'm not in need of any extra help right now though.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player meets the quest's requirements:}}
** '''Elias White:''' How kind of you to offer. I definitely wouldn't complain about some extra support, if you're sure you're interested?
* {{tselect|Start the Defender of Varrock quest?}}
* {{topt|Yes.}}
** '''Player:''' Absolutely! So what was this tip-off you received?
** '''Elias White:''' It's nothing much, but apparently one of the patrons in here was ranting and raving about zombies. Most just dismissed him as having had one too many, but I'm not so sure.
** '''Player:''' How come?
** '''Elias White:''' Varrock has an interesting history when it comes to zombies. Tell me, what do you know of Arrav?
** '''Player:''' Arrav? As in the Shield of Arrav? I was the one who helped return it to the museum.
** '''Elias White:''' Ah, I heard about that. Excellent work! You may well know then that the former owner of that shield, Arrav himself, once defended Varrock against a zombie invasion led by a Mahjarrat named Zemouregal.
** '''Elias White:''' Arrav sacrificed himself to save his city, but Zemouregal survived.
** '''Player:''' And you think these zombie sightings mean he's returned?
** '''Elias White:''' Apparently the zombies were seen forming ranks. Zombies don't naturally organise themselves, so someone must be organising them. I can think of worse candidates than Zemouregal.
** '''Player:''' I can see why you think this is worth looking into. Where do we start?
** '''Elias White:''' Zombies are not particularly light on their feet, so my hope is we can pick up their trail. The sightings were apparently right outside the inn.
** '''Player:''' Follow the tracks and see where they came from. Good plan.
** '''Elias White:''' Then shall we get started?
** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
** {{topt|Ready when you are.}}
*** '''Player:''' Ready when you are.
*** '''Elias White:''' Excellent! I'm right behind you.
*** {{tact|(Elias begins to follow the player.)}}
*** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
*** {{topt|Let's get going}}
**** '''Player:''' Let's get going.
**** '''Elias White:''' Lead the way.
**** {{tact|end}}
*** {{topt|What can you tell me about Arrav and Zemouregal?}}
**** '''Player:''' What can you tell me about Arrav and Zemouregal?
**** '''Elias White:''' It's quite the tale and I doubt I'd be able to do it justice, but I can try and give you an overview.
**** '''Elias White:''' Back in the Fourth Age, a group of travellers came upon an abandoned child. It is said the child was unusual for one so young. Dark eyes and a fierce countenance, yet fair hair and skin, with a kind smile.
**** '''Elias White:''' The travellers saw this as an omen and set up camp where they found him. The camp soon grew into the town of Avarrocka, or Varrock as we now call it.
**** '''Elias White:''' As for the child, he grew to become a mighty hero. After defending the town from a goblin attack, he took on the name Arrav, a curse word in goblin tongue, for he had become the Curse of Goblins.
**** '''Elias White:''' Arrav's heroic deeds continued, until he was granted a vision of the future. He saw the Mahjarrat Zemouregal claiming Avarrocka as his own.
**** '''Elias White:''' Determined to stop Zemouregal in any way he could, Arrav set out to find a powerful weapon with which to best him. His journey took him to the Imcando Dwarves, who granted him a powerful shield.
**** '''Player:''' The Shield of Arrav?
**** '''Elias White:''' Exactly. With the shield in hand, Arrav returned home and faced off against Zemouregal and his zombie horde. Thanks to him, the invasion was repelled, but at the cost of Arrav's life.
**** '''Elias White:''' Zemouregal has not been seen since, but it is said that his last act before retreating was to claim Arrav's body, promising to turn him into an undead slave to one day return with.
**** '''Elias White:''' Hundreds of years have now passed, and while there are few who haven't heard of Arrav, many have forgotten Zemouregal and his promise.
**** {{tact|other}}
*** {{topt|So what exactly is it you're researching?}}
**** '''Player:''' So what exactly is it you're researching?
**** '''Elias White:''' The Mahjarrat. It's fair to say they are quite the subject of fascination for me. Many of them once held dominion over huge parts of the world. Zamorak himself was a Mahjarrat, and he managed to achieve godhood!
**** '''Elias White:''' But now, they've all but vanished! Most will go through their whole lives without ever seeing one, and their most common appearance these days is in the spooky stories parents use to keep their children in line.
**** '''Player:''' And that's why you're so interested in Zemouregal?
**** '''Elias White:''' Indeed. An actual Mahjarrat, and a very dangerous one at that. Ancient tomes can only teach us so much. If I want to learn everything there is to know about their race, it's going to take some more hands on work.
**** '''Player:''' What about the danger?
**** '''Elias White:''' Well that's just all the more reason for me to be here. If Zemouregal is planning a new attack on Varrock, an expert on his race might come in quite useful.
**** {{tact|other}}
*** {{topt|If you're an explorer, I'm guessing you travel a lot?}}
**** '''Player:''' If you're an explorer, I'm guessing you travel a lot?
**** '''Elias White:''' Indeed! From the frozen wastes of the north to the ancient tombs of the desert, I've seen it all.
**** '''Player:''' So where do you call home?
**** '''Elias White:''' I've lived in many places over the years, but I wouldn't really say I have a home. I guess here in Varrock would be the closest answer.
**** '''Player:''' Sounds like you have quite the history.
**** '''Elias White:''' Oh yes! If nothing else, I've definitely lived a varied life.
**** '''Player:''' So you weren't always an explorer?
**** '''Elias White:''' Not at all. I've done all sorts of things in my time. In fact, at one point I was an adventurer like you!
**** '''Player:''' What happened? Some sort of life-changing injury?
**** '''Elias White:''' Thankfully not. I just found that when it came to my work, it was the history I discovered that interested me more than the treasure.
**** '''Player:''' Fair enough.
**** {{tact|other}}
*** {{topt|I need to do something else.}}
**** '''Player:''' I need to do something else.
**** {{tact|end}}
