==The Sacred Forge==
===Talking to Elias White===
* '''Elias White:''' Ah, there you are. How did things go after I left you?
* '''Player:''' Not good. Zemouregal is nearly ready to begin another attack on Varrock.
* '''Elias White:''' Then it's just as I feared. I've already reported our discovery to Captain Rovin. Come, let's fill him in on everything else you've learnt.
* {{tbox|You head upstairs with Elias.}}
* '''Captain Rovin:''' About time, adventurer. Your companion here tells me we have a zombie army on our doorstep!
* '''Elias White:''' I'm afraid that's not all, Captain. [player name] has made some further discoveries.
* '''Player:''' Indeed. Zemouregal plans to have Arrav lead the zombies in an attack on Varrock, and he plans to do so very soon.
* '''Captain Rovin:''' Zemouregal attacking Varrock again is our greatest fear and worst nightmare. And to think he now has Arrav under his control as well... What a horrifying fate for our greatest hero.
* '''Player:''' There may still be hope for Arrav. While spying on Zemouregal, I came face to face with him. He may serve Zemouregal, but not willingly. His mind is still his own.
* '''Elias White:''' A zombie with his mind intact... Most zombies are mere husks, their souls having long departed their bodies. For one to still be sentient is highly unusual. Could it mean...
* '''Player:''' What?
* '''Elias White:''' Oh, nothing to worry about now. Still, we may be able to work with this. What did Arrav have to say to you?
* '''Player:''' He told me that Zemouregal has his heart.
* '''Elias White:''' His heart? Interesting... Could that be how Zemouregal is controlling him?
* '''Captain Rovin:''' What are you saying? Does this mean we might be able to save Arrav?
* '''Elias White:''' In the long term, potentially. But this will require a fair amount of research. Something I fear we have little time for right now.
* '''Captain Rovin:''' Well then what other options do we have?
* '''Elias White:''' Well thanks to our good friend here, we have the very shield that was used to stop Zemouregal the first time he attacked.
* '''Captain Rovin:''' The Shield of Arrav? But is it really any use? Despite our attempts, we've never been able to unlock its power. Could it be that the legends were exaggerated and that it's just an ordinary shield?
* '''Elias White:''' To answer that, our best bet would likely be to seek out the creators of the shield: The Imcando Dwarves of Camdozaal.
* '''Captain Rovin:''' Hmm... but are the Imcando not extinct now?
* '''Player:''' Not quite. There are still a few out there, including one in Camdozaal. Ramarno is his name.
* '''Captain Rovin:''' Well then what are we waiting for? [player name], speak to this Ramarno and seek his advice on how to use the shield to defend our city. In the meantime, we will prepare our defences.
* {{tact|end}}

