===Talking to Ramarno===
* '''Player:''' Hello again.
* '''Ramarno:''' Ah, [player name]. I'm sure you have plenty of questions. I will do my best to answer them.
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|quest=No|What can I do here?}}
* {{topt|I need your help with a shield.}}
** '''Player:''' I need your help with a shield.
** '''Ramarno:''' A shield? What kind of shield?
** '''Player:''' The Shield of Arrav. We've discovered that Zemouregal intends to attack the city of Varrock with a zombie army. It was the shield that stopped him last time.
** '''Ramarno:''' Ah, and you are hoping to use it to do so again. I wish I could help you, but I know little of the shield and its power. It was created far before my time.
** '''Ramarno:''' Still, I may have a way for you to learn what you need.
** '''Player:''' How?
** '''Ramarno:''' The Sacred Forge of course!
** '''Player:''' But how will a forge help me?
** '''Ramarno:''' The Sacred Forge is far more than a mere furnace! It is a powerful relic from a time when the gods still walked these lands.
** '''Ramarno:''' Before Camdozaal's ruin, our sages would use the forge to guide our people. It is said the forge granted them access to the Dream Theatre, a place where they were blessed with visions of the past, present and future.
** '''Player:''' I see. So how do I access this Dream Theatre?
** '''Ramarno:''' The Forge will need powering, but normal barronite won't work for this. You'll need to obtain some imbued barronite. With that, provided the forge deems you worthy, you will be able to enter the Dream Theatre.
** '''Player:''' And how do I get imbued barronite?
** '''Ramarno:''' Head to the mines and mine yourself a barronite deposit. Once you have that, imbue it using the core of a chaos golem from the golem workshop.
